Award winning sports presenter Mpho Letsholonyane will be making her return to popular sports channel, Supersport today. This follows after she wrapped up her duties at the public broadcaster SABC yesterday where she announced on her social media that she was bidding the public broadcaster farewell. Speaking to Daily Sun, she said: "I am really happy about this and I feel it happened at the right time.” Mpho started her broadcasting career with youth radio station, YFM and made a move into television when she joined Supersport almost a decade ago in 2009. She then joined SABC in 2013, hosted shows like SAFAtv which aired on SABC1 every Saturday at 1:30pm and she was also co-hosting on Metro FM’s breakfast show, hosting a sports show on Thursdays from 18:00-19:20pm.   